data.enText: if a government or other group or person with authority repeals a law, that law is no longer valid

simple_means.memory_skill: re 相反；反对；不 + peal 呼吁 → 不呼吁 → 取消

example: He revoked the ban on smoking

value.def: If the government repeals a law, it officially ends it, so that it is no longer valid.

example.ex: The government has just repealed the law segregating public facilities.
example.tran: 政府刚刚废止了不同种族分开使用公共设施的法令。

example.ex: Next year will be the 60th anniversary of the repeal of Prohibition.
example.tran: 明年将是禁酒令废除60周年。
